  <brief_summary>
    <textblock>
      Our objective is to allow positive MRI diagnosis of vestibular neuritis by highlighting
      contrast enhancement of the vestibular nerve on the pathological side of the FLAIR sequence
      acquired 1h after intravenous gadolinium injection in patients with typical vestibular
      neuritis. At present, the diagnosis is based on a combination clinical examination /
      video-head impulse test, and no imaging examination allows the diagnosis to be positive.
    </textblock>
  </brief_summary>
